comments.body: Thanks, but credit is due to Dr. J-F Landry (CNC) who provided the information in a private communication.

From what I've been able to find out today and to clarify then...

MPG used to call the species in the image above 01134 -  Oegoconia quadripuncta Four-spotted Yellowneck hence my original ID.

Oegoconia novimundi which is found in western NA is now called 01134 - Four-spotted Yellowneck Moth.

The one that we have here in ON is 01134.01 – Oegoconia deauratella - Scarce Obscure.

Oegoconia quadripuncta is only found in Europe.

I'm not sure when all this happened but much thanks to mothmannb for pointing this out!

Not sure what happened above but no matter... I wasn't aware that there was a look-a-like species to 1134 – Oegoconia novimundi – Four-spotted Yellowneck! The mpg map indicates novimundi being in ON. Thanks for this...
seems the iNat is confused about these 2 species; that* comment is not mine!
